  "notes": "Samogitian (žemaitėška / žemaitiu kalba), an East Baltic variety of north-western Lithuania, treated by some as a dialect of Lithuanian and by others as a separate language. Its orthography is Lithuanian-based with five extra long vowels written with macrons (ā ē ī ō ū, plus ė̄) and the digraphs ⟨ou⟩ and ⟨ėi⟩ for two additional diphthongs. Pitch accent and the broken tone are not written and are not modelled. Metadata verified from the English Wikipedia article; the fact table supplied no Wikidata row for this code.",
